name: American River College
directions: Student center, down the hallway near Starbucks, out the door to the right, there is a single stall gender neutral bathroom (and also two gender specific bathrooms).

name: HMart
directions: In the back of the store on the right.
comment: Two individual restrooms

name: Saturn Cafe
directions: You have to ask for the key usually, but they're not treated as gendered.
comment: There are two restrooms, marked Robots and Aliens. Staff doesn't treat them as gendered when you get the key.

name: Hunter College
directions: There is a gender neutral bathroom on the 3rd floor of the Thomas Hunter building.
comment: You need to be a student there in order to get inside the building

name: Smith Building
directions: Basement floor (right next to a hallway of offices)

name: Chop's Deli Monkey Junction
directions: In back of store
comment: Prefer that you're a paying customer, but they won't stop you if you have to go.

name: Pleiades Gallery
directions: In back of gallery
comment: Browse and check out the art for a bit

name: 4214 N High St, Columbus, OH 43214, USA
Titsa, bus station
directions: In the lower part of the bus station and in front of the tramway, it's right behind (almost hidden) the "kioskos", those are little places where candies, lotery numbers or bus tickets are sold (you will notice right when you see the food they sell).
comment:
They are gendered bathrooms but no one notice the people that enters there, there aren't much people the most of times. 
Alert: it's a cruising place, so just do your thing and get out (anyway, people don't do anything to you, but I don't like or recomend to go alone).

name: Centro comercial Alcampo La Laguna
directions: It's in the low floor and near the cinema, under the parking; it's in the restautants' side. In the opposite side of the given street.
comment: You need to ask for the code or key to a waiter or waitress of one of the restaurants in the low floor, near the cinema. There is one restaurant which makes "arepas" (you can see that word on the name of the local) where the people is quite nice, so you don't have to pay/eat something to get access.

name: Liberty Center Mall
directions: Two unisex single occupancy restrooms are located on the first floor of the Foundry Building.  Park on the north side of the mall, and use the first floor entrance under the "Food Hall" sign.  The restrooms are located just inside the doors down a hallway to the right.

name: QuEST Building, Quinsigamond Community College
comment: New science building has multiple gendered faculty single-seater bathrooms, and I think family unisex ones too. Faculty ones may require keys. Bathrooms include accessibility railings, but doors/locks are not automatic. Flushing, soap, and water are all on sensors so are automatic.

name: Walmart
directions: Back of the store, between shoe department and photo/electronics.
comment: "Family restroom," single stall, handicap accessible.

name: AlMar
directions: In the back past the bar. Gender neutral single
comment: Fancy-ish restaurant, should be a paying customer

name: Superfine
directions: To the left up a short flight of stairs just in the entrance. Gendered single room
comment: This is a bar and restaurant, should probably pay but unlikely to notice

name: Sur Lie
directions: Once inside, straight back past the bar. Two single-occupant, ungendered restrooms.
comment: You might want to ask first? Probably if you say you need an ungendered restroom, you'll have no issue. Otherwise, perhaps order a soda at the bar first or after.

name: Walker Art Center
directions: Fifth floor of theater tower outside Skyline Room.  Also, two staff unisex single units on level M by offices.

name: Frontier
directions: Inside the mill building main entrance, bear right at the radio station, turn left at the end of the hall. Continue forward into the restaurant. Once inside, the bathrooms are down towards the back (away from the bar) and through a white door on the left. Two single-occupant, non-gendered separate rooms. Each is handicap accessible and child-friendly.
comment: This is specific to the Frontier restaurant and theater. Information on other businesses which share the building is unknown.

name: Venable Bistro
directions: Two gender neutral restrooms in the back right area of the restaurant.

name: B-Side Lounge
directions: through the first door on your left upon entering the room, there is a corridor that leads to 2 gender neutral bathrooms

name: The Hamilton
directions: Upstairs lounge has 2 unisex single bathrooms. Turn left at the top of the stairs.
comment: Basement venue bathrooms are gendered. Not sure about ground floor.

name: Algonquin Commons
directions: 2nd floor and the far right next to the silent study room

name: Global Gifts Short North
directions: Inside store.

name: Moose Jaw Public Library
directions: Gendered single stall washrooms are located on the main floor. Go through the main entrance and you will find the washrooms ahead and on the right.
comment: This is a public building.

name: Kaiser Permanente Endocrinology
directions: Second floor
comment: Open to the public, no appointment or check in required.

name: Asheville Raven and Crone
directions: There is a community room in the back of store..past free tea samples the bathroom is in left.
comment: Locally female owned bussiness please support and buy something. Note at right of front door the beautiful mission statement on the door.

name: Taquerito Real
comment: Debes consumir para acceder

name: Taquerito Real
comment: Debes consumir para acceder al baño

name: Crystal Bridges Museum of American Art
directions: Each restroom has a single person family restroom or a single person unisex restroom
comment: Always free admission during business hours. Museum is closed on Tuesdays.

name: 1488 Adanac St, Vancouver, BC V5L 2C3, Canada
Warren Wilson College
directions: Gladfelter Building (Dining Hall & Downstairs)
comment: The entire campus of Warren Wilson College is very trans inclusive and any space in general should be a safe space for LGBT.

name: Movie Tavern
directions: Walk in and walk straight across into the small hallway. It's labeled as a "family restroom."
comment: You do not have to be a paying customer.

name: Liquid Bread Gastropub
directions: Back of the restaurant

name: Vapor Icing Cafe
directions: Back left of store or ask
comment: Owners are extremely laid back and cool. Stop and try some juices and hang out!

name: Talon Vapor
directions: Very back of store
comment: Great if you vape, just try some juices. Owner of store is very cool with trans* people.

name: Tops for Shoes
directions: All bathrooms are gender neutral. Wheelchair accessible bathrooms located of the main entrance.
comment: Just come in and use the bathroom if you need. The shoes are pretty awesome, though. 🙂

name: Earle Hall Honors College
directions: Through the wooden double doors and 2nd door to the left on your left

name: Arch Climbing
directions: turn left upon entrance

name: Counter Tools
directions: Lots of bathrooms for gender neutral use in the 205 Lloyd Street building. Ours is upstairs so not accessible but private.

name: Zapow Art Gallery
comment: Zapow has listed on their FB page that they are accepting of all genders, gender identity, and sexual identities.

name: Public Library
directions: Across from librarians desk. Gender neutral single stall bathroom
comment:
Mon, Tues, Fri 1pm-6pm
Wed 2pm-8pm
Thurs 10am-6pm

name: Health Emergency Lifeline Program
directions: Three accessible and one non-accessible single occupant, gender neutral restrooms. Also, waiting room is a safe space, and staff and programs are gender-affirming.
comment:
Waiting room is open to all, as is one accessible restroom. 
Must become a client for additional services.

name: Zingerman's Deli
directions: Enter the Deli (brick building ) and go rightt, head towards the back. The bathroom is behind the freezer on the left, just before the stairs. It is marked "gender inclusive"
comment: Ask any staff member for help if you can't find the bathroom. The staff is known for being friendly and inclusive.

name: Mitchell Community College Montgomery Student Union Building
directions: First floor, under the stairs on either side of the front entrance.
comment: These are recently made gender-neutral so the one on the right has a urinal and the one on the left does not.

name: The Copper Onion
comment: It's a pricier restaurant but the food is fantastic. There are two gender-neutral single-stall bathrooms. I was there some time ago and don't remember if it was accessible or not, so marked it not to avoid misleading anyone, but it may be.

name: Watauga Medical Center
directions: First floor in the laboratory/X-ray waiting room.

name: OHM Advisors
comment: Private engineering firm, most folks won't have need to come in, but if you do there are two single stall unisex restrooms at the front.

name: Nordstrom
comment: It's a department store. So you may want to browse. It's a large family bathroom.

name: West Valley Branch Public Library
directions: Family restroom near the children's area; not near the multi-stall gendered ones you see when you walk in.

name: Munson Medical Center
directions: Walk in main doors, up the stairs/ramp and turn left. Walk all the way down the hall until you see 2 unisex restrooms on your left.
comment: Parking lot is free. Bike racks also available. Just walk right in and use the restroom. I'm not sure if either of these are accessible. One of them might be.

name: Ivy Tech Community College
directions: In "student commons"(aka the cafeteria area). There are three bathrooms men's, women's, and a single stall unisex bathroom.
comment: Large, single stall. No bathroom hook to hang coat. Sink turns on automatically.

name: Dogstar Tattoo Company
comment: Welcome!

name: Temescal Alley
directions: Next to Cro Cafe
comment: It's usually unlocked. If not, ask for the key at the Cro Cafe or another shop.

name: Lowes
directions: Front of the building next to the gendered bathrooms - look to the right just before the employee break room
comment: No one questions your use of this restroom AND it is generally very clean and well stocked!

name: Next Door Bake Shop
directions: In the back- ask where it is and lock the top lock not the door knob!

name: Adams County Library System
directions: Third floor, near elevator.
comment: Two restrooms, one labeled 'mens' and one 'women's' (but they're single stall and no one's there to see you/judge)

name: Adams County Library System
directions: Second floor, near elevator.
comment: You have to get a key from the desk.

name: Magic Wand Restaurant
directions: Down the hallway in the back.
comment: You could probably get away with not buying anything, but the food is good and reasonably priced.

name: Periscope Studio
directions: Fifth floor. Stick your head in at Suite 500 (keep turning right) and ask any of us for a key!
comment: Locked, gendered two-stall bathrooms are shared with a couple other small offices, but one of us is happy to escort you and make sure you feel safe and/or have the bathroom to yourself.

name: Vineyard Haven Public Library
directions: Main floor, to the left just after the entrance.
comment: Safe space, single person bathrooms, welcome to come in just to use the restroom.

name: MIT Student Center
directions: In the basement near the post office and the dry cleaners.  For those familiar with MIT campus this is building W20 - across the street from the dome.
comment: This is a public building so anyone can use it.  Single seat wheelchair accessible facility with a door that locks.

name: YWCA Greensboro
directions: First and second floor has multiple stall gender neutral bathrooms and on the first floor there is a private all genders/family bathroom
comment: The YWCA Greensboro is dedicated to eliminating racism, empowering women and promoting peace, justice, freedom and dignity for all. An injustice anywhere is an injustice everywhere.

name: Stallions Entertainment Complex
directions: well marked
comment: Open 7pm to 2am

name: First Congregational UCC in Brainerd
directions: Main floor - two single use, gender neutral restrooms. Accessible for use during office hours (M-F 8am-12pm) and during Sunday worship 10am-11am

name: First Congregational UCC in Brainerd
directions: Main floor - two sing use, gender neutral restrooms. Accessible for use during office hours (M-F 8am-12pm) and during Sunday worship 10am-11am

name: MAHEC OBGYN
comment: Single occupancy, gender neutral bathrooms available for patients

name: Walgreens
directions: In the stock room (need to be let in by employee).
comment: Need to be given access by employee (behind locked door). One bathroom for all genders.

name: Levine Museum of the New South
directions: 1st floor towards back of building
comment: Paying customer, or someone who wants to look at the Visit Charlotte tourist information wall. You can also browse the store

name: Fenway Community Health
directions: There are 2 on every floor, to the left and around behind the elevators.
comment: Open 8am-7pm. You do not have to be a patient.

name: Pavement Coffee
directions: Down hallway by the espresso bar, to the far right of the service counter. 2 accessible single person unisex restrooms.
comment: Technically for customers only, but the staff are generally too busy to enforce that.

name: Durham Co-op Market
directions: Straight to the back of the store

name: Starbucks
directions: Once inside the building turn to your right and walk all the way back.

name: Stingers Coffee
directions: Bathroom is adjacent to the office store door. The office store is directly in view when you walk through the front door.

name: Midtown Independence Title
directions: Off our front lobby
comment: Just ask our friendly receptionist and tell her Doug  sent you. (I am the Managing Director of the firm)

name: Duke University - Trent Hall
directions: third floor, hallway parallel to Erwin Road
comment: bathroom marked with an "All Gender Restroom" sign

name: Columbia Law School Jerome Greene Hall
directions: Third Floor. Right turn out of elevators.

name: Kroger Pharmacy
directions: Hidden in the corner near the pharmacy
comment: Two large, single-stall family restrooms with locking doors. No urinals. Excellent for changing or having a quiet space if panicking.

name: Pure Pizza
comment: Strong advocate for inclusion & equality!

name: East Carolina University
directions: Both sets are near SE corner of building.  Set 1: Second floor in back of building near biology labs; set 2: first floor just right of SE corner entrance. First set a little more private in terms of entry/exit.

name: Sweet Breads
directions: Two doors on the right in the back of the restaurant. Both are gender neutral single toilets. Beautiful restrooms!
comment: Beautiful, welcoming, friendly restaurant.

name: Amsterdam Museum
directions: On the same floor you enter the museum on, all the way in the back past the guards, staircases, lockers, and waiting area. It's up a couple of steps but the museum states that they also provide accessible toilet facilities.
comment: You do need a ticket to enter, but if you have any kind of Amsterdam museum pass you can go in as many times as you'd like. The main bathroom is two open rooms of private toilet stalls and a shared sink area.
